OL,7,FNHS Greater Glasgow and Clyde `
OL,8,FScotland's largest health board `
OL,9,Faccepted that "two families have been
OL,10,Fcaused significant additional distress
OL,11,Fat an already very difficult time" as
OL,12,Fa result of the incident.
OL,14,FIt is understood human error was to
OL,15,Fblame for the "wrongful release" of
OL,16,Fthe body from the health board's
OL,17,Fmortuary at the Queen Elizabeth
OL,18,FUniversity Hospital in Glasgow.
